review_blob: this is my favourite English IPA, the nose is grassy, pine and citrus bold fruity hops dance on the taste buds, body is a bit on the light side but still a very good beer from a very good brewery
From bottle. The nose is slight floral and sweet, taste is malty, floral and slight citrus. Mouth feel is lacking
From bottle . On the nose is citrus peel slight pine and slight metalic. Taste is citrus, floral and pine with sweet busicuity malt finish.
From bottle. Pours a cloudy pale gold with white head. One the nose is bright citrus and spice. Taste is spicy, floral and bready.
From bottle. Pours golden with rocky white head. Aroma is bread, grapefruit and alcohol. Taste is citrus, grapefruit, lime and alcohol.
From cask. Golden coper colour. Nose is ginger and orange peel. Taste is spicey, ginger and orange peel. Very nice, not what I was expecting.
from bottle. clean crisp refreshing taste, crystal clear. good classic pilsner
From bottle pours a pale golden colour with thick white head. Nose is slightly fruity and woody. Taste is bold hops and fruit
Nose is fruity and pine. Taste is fruit salad with a hop heavy finish. Sound brew
From bottle. Nose is clove,bread and banana. Taste is bready spicy clove slight alcohol. Head is 3 fingers.
Gravity fed pint at. CAMRA ulverston beer festival 2013. Nose is pine and citrus. Taste is again pine, citrus and floral.
On cask at kings arms barrow. Nose is bold citrus mostly orange and lemon with slight floral notes. Taste is bold citrus and pine. Lovely beer local favourite.
on the nose is slight floral and basement, taste is lightly sweet with dry finish, not bad for a mas produced lager
from bottle. nose is roasty, caramel and grain. taste is sweet roasty malts, coffee and chocolate. nice beer
from bottle. on the nose is grapefruit and pine. taste is floral and citrus rind with a nice hoppy bitter finish.
On draft at the kings arms barrow, A nice attempt at a pilsner, solid, crisp and refreshing
From bottle. Nose is peach and mango with slight pine. Taste is peach, pine and slight breadyness. Big hop flavour that lingers. Amazing.
From bottle. Nose is fresh meadow and floral. Taste is pine and and slight soapy with lingering hops on the palate.
From bottle. On the nose is big and citrus. Taste is piney with Some citrus and a sweet biscuity malt

From cask at the kings arms barrow. The nose is pine and resin and wood almost foresty. Aperance is pale gold with creamy white head. Taste is bold hops that ad pine and apricot with a lot of hop bitterness but not unpleasant quite the opposite
big fruity IPA nose is apple and dried fruit. taste is big bold fruity with sweet maltyness and slight alcohol.

tried draft and bottled several times in Amsterdam, faint spice and banana on the nose. taste is mild again a slight banana note. Better draft than bottled. when in Amsterdam I found this made a good alternative to the two main lagers as im not a huge fan of them. not a bad beer by any stretch of the imagination
single bottle bought as a gift from beers of Europe outstanding wheat beer. big spice, bubble gum and herbs. taste was similar clean and fresh would love to try again
full bottles sample. aroma is pine and citrus. taste is slight floral or pine with fruit mainly apricot. mouth feel is light and lively finish is hop bitter with lingering sweetness.
in bottle. pours hazy yellow big white head. on the nose is big spice, bread and faint banana. Taste was lacking on just about all aspects. mouth feel was watery. great brewery not there best beer.

On tap duke of Edinburgh barrow. On the nose big banana, spice and orange zest, mouth feel is slightly lacking some substance. Taste is bold banana and bubble gum. A good but not quit great wheat beer

On tap, north bar leeds. Wow wow wow. Smell is pine and yeast with apricot. Taste is hop bitter, malty sweet, bready and dried fruit. A fantastic beer on tap, sad it will be a long time before I try this again.
Tried at cafe golem amsterdam. Big Belgian blond, orange and spice on the nose. Taste was fruity,bread,slight alcohol.
The kings arms barrow. Nice blond ale, fruity on the nose, slight hop bitterness big fruity flavour
Tried at the kings arms hawcoat barrow. Nice Attempt at a American style pale, nice slight pine on the nose. Taste has some hop, could use some more but pleasantly fruity!
